metadata.symbol: so good it makes you sick
metadata.description: Watercolor painting I made n 1998 to illustrate my philosophy at that time about life. I had not read Neal Stephenson's book yet. This was my first foray into remixing digital and analog. Creating images that commented on the digital world using analog media. The original print no longer exists.

metadata.subtitle: in the beginning there was the command line
